<file path="README.md">
 1: # SaaS & Startup Astro & Tailwind CSS Template
 2: 
 3: ## License
 4: 
 5: This template is open-source software licensed under the [GPL-3.0 license](https://opensource.org/licenses/GPL-3.0). You are free to fork, modify, and use it in your projects.
 6: 
 7: ## Attribution
 8: 
 9: Originally created by Michael Andreuzza. Modified, extended, and redistributed by Bektur Aslan with added sections and updated UI/UX for broader usage.
10: 
11: ## This template is using Tailwind CSS V4
12: 
13: Now we are using only a CSS file. It's called `global.css` and it's located in the src/styles folder. Now we are eimporting Tailwind CSS on the same file instead of using the `tailwind.config.cjs` file. Like this:
14: 
15: ```css
16: // Importing Tailwind CSS
17: @import "tailwindcss";
18: // Importing Tailwind plugins
19: @plugin "@tailwindcss/typography";
20: @plugin "@tailwindcss/forms";
21: ```
22: 
23: Then to add your styles you will use the @theme directive. Like this:
24: 
25: ```css
26: @theme {
27:   /* Your CSS goes here, see how styles are written on the global.css file */
28: }
29: ```
30: 
31: Remember this is just in Alpha version, so you can use it as you want. Just keep an eye on the changes that Tailwind CSS is going to make.
32: 
33: ## Template Structure
34: 
35: Inside of your Astro project, you'll see the following folders and files:
36: 
37: ```
38: /
39: ├── public/
40: ├── src/
41: │   └── pages/
42: │       └── index.astro
43: └── package.json
44: ```
45: 
46: Astro looks for `.astro` or `.md` files in the `src/pages/` directory. Each page is exposed as a route based on its file name.
47: 
48: There's nothing special about `src/components/`, but that's where we like to put any Astro/React/Vue/Svelte/Preact components.
49: 
50: Any static assets, like images, can be placed in the `public/` directory.
51: 
52: ## Commands
53: 
54: All commands are run from the root of the project, from a terminal:
55: 
56: | Command                | Action                                           |
57: | :--------------------- | :----------------------------------------------- |
58: | `npm install`          | Installs dependencies                            |
59: | `npm run dev`          | Starts local dev server at `localhost:3000`      |
60: | `npm run build`        | Build your production site to `./dist/`          |
61: | `npm run preview`      | Preview your build locally, before deploying     |
62: | `npm run astro ...`    | Run CLI commands like `astro add`, `astro check` |
63: | `npm run astro --help` | Get help using the Astro CLI                     |
64: 
65: ## Want to learn more?
66: 
67: Feel free to check Astro's [documentation](https://docs.astro.build)
